        <div id="dsq-comment-body-15721" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-15721" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>I do not believe that Bitcoin mining is environmentally irresponsible in general; I in fact argued quite the opposite in my article here: http://bitcoinmagazine.net/the-wasted-electricity-objection-to-bitcoin/ . What is irresponsible is deliberately mining on highly suboptimal hardware. Since you&#8217;ll be mining on everyday GPUs rather than the specially designed chips that everyone else will be on in a couple of years, the electricity cost spent on mining will drastically exceed the revenue that you receive, and the only way such a situation can possibly exist is due to the fact that (most) users don&#8217;t have access to an itemized list of just how many dollars of electricity everything costs. We have to mine, but we should mine in ways that make sense.</p>
</div>
